    "summary": "My Iconic*story\n\nAlready since my dance academy years I have initiated choreographic and interdisciplinary collaborations. I have always been interested in creating remarkable rituals with moving , singing and talking bodies in performances outside the theatre walls. I professionalised my passion for immersive and multi-disciplinary performance in art projects and commercial settings ( events , clubs, restaurant).\n\nDuring my studies at the master DAS: Creative Producing (2018-2020) I toured with an art installation about iconic love stories within the LGBTQI+ community: celebrating the 20 year mark of same-sex weddings in the Netherlands.\n\nIn the early nineties I graduated in Theater Science (University of Utrecht) and Modern Theater Dance (Amsterdam School of the Arts). Shortly after, I followed my heart to the source of modern dance in New York City and studied with postmodernist masters Merce Cunningham and Erick Hawkins. \n\nBack in Amsterdam I danced many years in the company of Truus Bronkhorst & Marien Jongewaard (amongst others) during which I started creating my own performances in the clubscene and event sector next to building an international career in dance education.",
